solution: ```class Solution {
    public int minimumScore(String s, String t) {
        int n = s.length(), m = t.length();
        int[] left = new int[m + 1];
        int[] right = new int[m + 1];
        Arrays.fill(left, m);
        Arrays.fill(right, -1);
        left[0] = -1;
        for (int i = 0, j = 0; i < n && j < m; ++i) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j)) {
                left[j + 1] = j;
                ++j;
            }
        }
        right[m] = m;
        for (int i = n - 1, j = m - 1; i >= 0 && j >= 0; --i) {
            if (s.charAt(i) == t.charAt(j)) {
                right[j] = j;
                --j;
            }
        }
        int res = m;
        for (int l = 0, r = 0; l <= m; ++l) {
            while (r <= m && left[l] + 1 > right[r]) ++r;
            if (r <= m) res = Math.min(res, r - l);
        }
        return res;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n + m)
space complexity: O(m)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Precompute the longest prefix of t that is a subsequence of s (left array) and the longest suffix of t that is a subsequence of s (right array). Then binary-search the smallest window [l, r) of t to remove so that the concatenation of the prefix up to l and the suffix from r is a subsequence of s.

